{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04249/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04249"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:42:49"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld, pan, tracking"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["group shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman carrying a card with the number \"20\" exits a room of fashion spectators."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04249/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04249","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04249/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04249"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04249/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04249/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04249/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04249/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04249/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04249/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04249/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04249/canvas/1/7cf090d2-d2c3-4a31-a0d1-d6d10d06e11c","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:28:27.090Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>A part of the fashion show, the dress numbers underscore how the women in these situations and in the world of haute couture fashion houses were material and commodities. In this way, they function similarly to the measurements in the scene when Alma meets Cyril. This detail also seems to be drawn from Mary Blume’s biography of Cristóbal Balenciaga: “Like Vionnet, Balenciaga wanted his models to be remote rather than appealing, gazing over the heads of clients and casually carrying a card on which the number of the outfit—unlike other designers, he never gave his clothes names—was displayed” (Blume, <em>The Master of Us All</em>,34).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04249/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:843.71467025572,805.5181695827725,387.6177658142667,262.2880215343205"}}}]}]}]}